    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2), a definitive example of analog precision. This specimen is powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus, delivering linear power to an advanced viscous-coupling AWD system through a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis benefits from the factory wide-body architecture and is equipped with Turbo-spec suspension geometry and Brembo four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors. Meticulously maintained with a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recent borescope inspection confirming zero cylinder scoring. The original paint retains its deep luster, and the undercarriage is free of any fluid seepage or oxidation. This is an uncompromising, turnkey investment for the serious driver.",
